<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <meta charset='utf-8'>
    <meta http-equiv='X-UA-Compatible' content='IE=edge'>
    <title>Charlzk05 - Image Resizer</title>
    <meta name='viewport' content='width=device-width, initial-scale=1'>
    <link rel='stylesheet' type='text/css' media='screen' href='main.css'>
    <link rel="icon" type="image/x-icon" href="Resources/github logo.ico">
</head>
<body>
    <div class="backgroundImage"></div>
    <div class="topBar">
        <h3>Charlzk05 Image Resizer</h3>
    </div>
    <div class="main">
        <div class="formContainer">
            <form action="/resize" method="post" enctype="multipart/form-data">
                <input name="file" type="file" accept=".png,.jpeg,.jpg,.gif,.webp,.avif">
                <p>Supported formats: PNG, JPG, JPEG, GIF, WEBP, AVIF</p>
                <div class="textInputs">
                    <p>New Width <span>by pixel</span></p>
                    <input type="text" name="width" placeholder="1920">
                    <p style="margin-top: 10px;">New Height <span>by pixel</span></p>
                    <input type="text" name="height" placeholder="1080">
                </div>
                <input type="submit" value="Resize" id="submitButton" disabled>
            </form>
            <div class="about">
                <h2>Charlzk05 Image Resizer</h2>
                <p>When the size of your photos is important, you frequently have to sacrifice their quality. But you don't have to make this sacrifice with Charlzk05 Image Resizer! You can resize your images and GIFs without losing quality. Charlzk05 Image Resizer does not require the installation of any additional software on your computer to function.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <script src='main.js'></script>
</body>
</html>